# CAD Module — Boundary Rules

## Module Structure

The CAD studio is made up of three component folders and three pages:

- `src/components/text-to-cad/` — Full Text-to-CAD authoring studio
- `src/components/cad/` — CAD Studio landing (ring preview, viewer, toolbars)
- `src/components/cad-studio/` — Shared materials, viewport, and inspector (used by both Text-to-CAD and CAD-to-Catalog)
- `src/pages/CADStudio.tsx` — Hub/landing page at `/studio-cad`
- `src/pages/TextToCAD.tsx` — Full studio page at `/text-to-cad`
- `src/pages/CADToCatalog.tsx` — CAD-to-Catalog page at `/cad-to-catalog`

## Visual Layer — DO NOT TOUCH

These files control what is rendered in 3D. **Do not modify them** in any way that could alter geometry, materials, lighting, camera, or render output. Treat them as sealed, protected dependencies.

- `src/components/text-to-cad/CADCanvas.tsx` — main 3D canvas, GLB loader, TransformControls, mesh selection, materials rendering
- `src/components/cad-studio/materials.ts` — material definitions that drive the visual appearance of all 3D surfaces; do not change constant values or type shapes

If you need to wire new behaviour into the canvas, do it via its existing **props interface** and **ref handle** only. Do not add rendering logic inside the file.

## Control Layer — Safe to Restyle

These files handle user interaction with the 3D scene. They can be restyled, restructured, or refactored as needed, as long as the **props/API contract with CADCanvas is preserved**.

- `src/components/text-to-cad/LeftPanel.tsx` — left sidebar: prompt input, model selector, quick edits, generate/edit actions
- `src/components/text-to-cad/EditToolbar.tsx` — toolbar with transform/mesh/materials/display flyouts
- `src/components/text-to-cad/MeshPanel.tsx` — right sidebar mesh list
- `src/components/text-to-cad/ViewportOverlays.tsx` — overlays: progress, action buttons, stats bar

## Shared Types — Partially Safe

- `src/components/text-to-cad/types.ts` — structure and locations can be changed; **do not change constant values** (e.g. `QUICK_EDITS`, `AI_MODELS`, `TRANSFORM_MODES`) that feed the renderer or drive the CAD pipeline.

## Deprecated Files — Do Not Use

These files exist for potential future use but are **not imported anywhere** in the current codebase. Do not add imports from them:

- `src/components/cad/CADViewport.tsx`
- `src/components/cad/ViewportToolbar.tsx`
- `src/components/cad/ViewportTopBar.tsx`
- `src/components/cad/MeshLibrary.tsx`
- `src/components/cad-studio/DiamondMaterial.tsx`

## Boundary Rules

- Non-CAD features **must not** import from inside the CAD component folders.
  - Good: import from `@/lib/azure-utils`, `@/lib/formanova-cad-api`, `@/lib/generation-history-api`
  - Bad: import from `@/components/text-to-cad/...`, `@/components/cad/...`, `@/components/cad-studio/...`
- The only connection between the app shell and the CAD module is via the three lazy-loaded page routes in `src/App.tsx`.
- Shared utilities (e.g. `azureUriToUrl`) belong in `src/lib/`, not inside CAD component files.
